did.unittitle: Office of the Vice Provost Records

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection contains some restricted material. Restrictions related to specific material are listed in the detailed contents list. The collection may require review before it is available for use. Please contact DCA for further details.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into three series: Funded grants, Boston Campus; Funded grants, Medford Campus; and 2017 accessions.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office of the Vice Provost was formerly known as the Office of the Associate Provost for Research. Between November 1984 and July 1986 the positions of Director of Government Resources, Health Sciences, and the Director of Government Resources, Arts and Sciences, were moved from the University Development office to the Office of the Senior Vice President and Provost with the creation of the positions of Associate Provost for Research, Boston Campus and the Associate Provost for Research, Medford Campus. The two positions were combined during the 1993-1994 academic year, and the position was also expanded to include the Grafton campus. In 2004, the Associate Provost for Research became the Vice Provost.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Dates at the item level are approximate. When materials were accessioned, they were separated into separate collections for the Medford and Boston campuses. DCA staff, including the Records Archivist, Records Manager and Director, determined that these were the same functional office with two sites, rather than two separate offices and the collections were merged on 2008-02-19. Boxes from Boston Campus are designated as such in the notes field; all other boxes are from the Medford office. Processing of the 2017 accessions was completed by Leah Edelman in 2017 and 2018. Materials were placed in archival boxes if the original housing was damaged, and loose materials were placed in folders where needed. Received order was maintained. A box-level inventory and series-level description were created and the finding aid was updated at the time of processing.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: These records consist of files related to funded grants consisting of, but not limited to: grant proposal narrative, budget, application form, and letters of support; notice of award from funding entity; Tufts Internal Notice of Award Form; Agreements/Contracts; F&A Tree Information Form; correspondence; no-Cost Extension Forms; progress and final reports; and Close Notices. These records primarily date from the mid 1980s onward. The function of these records is to document the process of funded grants at Tufts University. Materials are created by the grant applicants, related offices and departments, the Office of Research Administration and the Office of the Vice Provost. The Office of the Vice Provost is the holder of the official copy of these records.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproductions and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish. Copyright to all materials created by Tufts University employees in the course of their work is held by the Trustees of Tufts University.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Transferred by the Office of the Vice Provost, 2005-2017.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Records containing information related to student education, staff and faculty employment, and Board of Trustees records are closed for 75 years from the date of creation.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is arranged in order of accession.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains grant files for research completed on the Boston, Medford, and Grafton campuses between 1980 and 2016, as well as ORA Grant and Award files from FY12-FY14.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Records containing information related to student education, staff and faculty employment, and Board of Trustees records are closed for 75 years from the date of creation.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Transferred by Jonathan Chau, Office of the Vice Provost, 2017, accession UA-2018-029.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This sub-series is arranged in received order; received order is largely by fiscal year.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This sub-series contains ORA Grant and Award files from FY12-FY14.
